source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1969-1970, 1993, 2013 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2005; (f) only total population for 2003 Census; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the 1960-1961 DS and 2000, 2012, 2019-2021 DHS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2000; (b) birth-histories data from the 2000, 2012, 2019-2021 DHS; (c) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1993 Census; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1969-1970, 1993 censuses; (e) indirect estimates obtained from stable population assumption; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1993 Census and 2000, 2012, 2019-2021 DHS. In addition, the indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1956-1995 Education Stats have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) registered deaths by age and sex available through 1961; (b) The demographic impact of AIDS has been factored into the mortality estimates; (c) estimates using HIV/AIDS model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0) and adult mortality (45q15) with UNAIDS estimates of adult HIV prevalence, and ART coverage for children and adults. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) siblings deaths from the 2000, 2012, 2019-2021 DHS; (b) paternal orphanhood from the 2000 DHS; (c) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) maternal orphanhood from the 2000, 2012 DHS; (b) paternal orphanhood from the 2012 DHS have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) registered infant and child deaths through 1961; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2000, 2012 DHS; (c) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2019-2021 DHS have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
